document_title: Cosmetic (silicon) breast implant rupture: causes, signs and treatment
subsection_name: vo-tui-nguc.json_2_Common causes of breast implant rupture
subsection_content:
Everyday movement can eventually lead to normal wear and tear of the breast implant shell. However, there are factors that can cause breast implant shells to deteriorate faster:
Capsular contracture: the fibrous tissue that forms around the breast implant contracts and compresses the implant, potentially causing rupture; Filling above or below the implant.; Trauma to the chest.; Injuries caused by surgery.
